name: Strawberry
description: a sweet soft red fruit with a seed-studded surface.

name: Salmon
description: a large edible fish that is a popular game fish, much prized for its pink flesh. Salmon mature in the sea but migrate to freshwater streams to spawn.

name: Banana
description: a long curved fruit which grows in clusters and has soft pulpy flesh and yellow skin when ripe.

name: Orange
description: a round juicy citrus fruit with a tough bright reddish-yellow rind.

name: Chicken
description: a domestic fowl kept for its eggs or meat, especially a young one.

name: Apple
description: the round fruit of a tree of the rose family, which typically has thin red or green skin and crisp flesh. Many varieties have been developed as dessert or cooking fruit or for making cider.

name: Tuna
description: a large and active predatory schooling fish of the mackerel family. Found in warm seas, it is extensively fished commercially and is popular as a game fish.

name: Spinach
description: a widely cultivated edible Asian plant of the goosefoot family, with large, dark green leaves that are eaten raw or cooked as a vegetable.

name: Broccoli
description: a cultivated variety of cabbage bearing heads of green or purplish flower buds that are eaten as a vegetable.

name: Cabbage
description: a cultivated plant eaten as a vegetable, having thick green or purple leaves surrounding a spherical heart or head of young leaves.

name: Cheese
description: a food made from the pressed curds of milk.

name: Milk
description: an opaque white fluid rich in fat and protein, secreted by female mammals for the nourishment of their young.

name: Duck
description: a waterbird with a broad blunt bill, short legs, webbed feet, and a waddling gait.

name: Ketchup
description: a smooth sauce made chiefly from tomatoes and vinegar, used as a condiment.

name: Salt
description: a white crystalline substance that gives seawater its characteristic taste and is used for seasoning or preserving food.

name: Pepper
description: a pungent, hot-tasting powder prepared from dried and ground peppercorns, commonly used as a spice or condiment to flavor food.

name: Carrot
description: a tapering orange-colored root eaten as a vegetable.

name: Mushroom
description: a fungal growth that typically takes the form of a domed cap on a stalk, with gills on the underside of the cap.

name: Corn
description: a North American cereal plant that yields large grains, or kernels, set in rows on a cob. Its many varieties yield numerous products, highly valued for both human and livestock consumption.

name: Pear
description: a yellowish- or brownish-green edible fruit that is typically narrow at the stalk and wider toward the base, with sweet, slightly gritty flesh.
